		<td><b></b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />You could think as layers like that :
<br />
<br />Sprite w.o. priority bit -&gt; BG -&gt; Sprite with priority flag -&gt; BG color @ $3f00
<br />
<br />This isn't exactly true as priority is determined between sprites first, and then the priority of the "selected" sprite collides with BG. Castlevania uses this.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
